						               													<description>S&amp;auml;tt spr&amp;auml;tt p&amp;aring; en miljon, styled on covers as &amp;quot;S&amp;auml;tt spr&amp;auml;tt p&amp;aring; en milj000.000n&amp;quot;, was produced in-house by Swedish Alga with the same theme and overall structure as Go For Broke: players are heirs tasked with quickly spending (within arbitrary limits) a small portion of a heritage, hoping to win the remainder.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As in the older game, players move along spaces following instructions and participating in various activities like gambling and stock market speculation. Differences include the game track being broken up into themed sections, some of which players may loop through; in the use of event cards; and in the several card- and die-based minigames that take the place of spinners. There are also touches like each player role having a quirk with a minor mechanical effect.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is the first player to get rid of all their money, with the rest being ranked by how much money they have left (i.e. the player second closest to winning finishes last).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
